-- Strides Arcolab to Raise $100 Million Selling Shares to Large Investors
-- B y   P o o j a   T h a k u r
-- 2010-09-23T12:23:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/strides-arcolab-to-raise-100-million-selling-shares-to-large-investors.html
Strides Arcolab Ltd., an Indian
drugmaker, plans to raise as much as $100 million in a share
sale to large investors, according to a sale document obtained
by Bloomberg News.  The shares will be sold for at least 423.55 rupees each,
the document showed. IDFC Capital Ltd., Daiwa Capital Markets
India Pvt., Kotak Mahindra Capital Co. and RBS Equities (India)
Ltd. are managing the sale, the document showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pooja Thakur in Mumbai at 
 pthakur@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
